      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[AI] fix(agents): recover from non-resumable assistant tail by re-presenting last user message",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\r\n\r\nAfter gateway restart, sessions with text-only assistant-tail interruptions (agent replied with text, no tool calls, no approval pending) failed silently, forcing users to retype their request. The recovery code only handled raw API message formats and the physical last message, missing text-only canonical content-block representations and trailing system/compaction messages.\r\n\r\nThis PR recovers from that state by detecting the text-only tail, extracting the last user message from the transcript, and re-presenting it to the agent via `buildResumeMessage()` with an idempotency guard.\r\n\r\nTool-call tails and approval-pending tails remain fail-closed — the broader no-retype recovery policy for side-effecting tails is tracked in #95609.\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\n\r\n- Problem: Text-only assistant tails after gateway restart forced user retype\r\n- Solution: Extract last user message from transcript and re-present via `buildResumeMessage()` with idempotency guard\r\n- Scope: Text-only recovery. Tool-call and approval-pending tails still fail and prompt retype (#95609 stays open).\r\n\r\n## Evidence\r\n\r\n### Tier 1: Unit Tests (52 tests, all pass)\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/main-session-restart-recovery.test.ts --run --reporter verbose\r\n\r\n✓ recovers from non-resumable assistant tail by re-presenting last user message\r\n  → recoverRestartAbortedMainSessions returns { recovered: 1, failed: 0, skipped: 0 }\r\n  → resume message contains original user text wrapped in <untrusted-text>\r\n  → abortedLastRun cleared after recovery\r\n\r\n✓ falls back to unresumable notice when assistant tail has pending tool_calls\r\n  → tool-call tails remain fail-closed\r\n\r\n✓ still fails on stale approval-pending tool result tail\r\n  → approval tails remain fail-closed\r\n\r\nTests: 52 passed (52)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Tier 2: End-to-End Real Gateway Recovery 🔥\r\n\r\nA real gateway process is started with auth=none on loopback. A session with a text-only assistant tail is created, marked for recovery, and the production `recoverRestartAbortedMainSessions` is called — it connects to the running gateway via WebSocket (`callGateway({ method: \"agent\" })`) and resumes the session:\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ npx tsx proof-95899.mjs\r\n\r\nGateway: starting...\r\nGateway: ready ✓\r\n[main-session-restart-recovery] marked 1 interrupted main session(s) for restart recovery\r\nMark:     marked=1 abortedLastRun=true\r\n[main-session-restart-recovery] resumed interrupted main session: agent:ops:main\r\n[main-session-restart-recovery] main-session restart recovery complete: recovered=1 failed=0 skipped=0\r\nRecover:  recovered=1 failed=0 skipped=0\r\nSession:  status=running abortedLastRun=false\r\n\r\n✅ GATEWAY RESTART RECOVERY: recovered=1 failed=0\r\n   Text-only assistant tail → auto-resumed\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe proof script (`proof-95899.mjs`) is self-contained: it starts a minimal gateway, creates a session store + transcript, calls the production recovery pipeline, and verifies the result — all without mocking.\r\n\r\n### Recovery Behavior Matrix\r\n\r\n| Tail type | `recoverRestartAbortedMainSessions` result | User experience |\r\n|-----------|--------------------------------------------|-----------------|\r\n| Text-only assistant | `recovered=1` | Agent sees original request, continues |\r\n| Tool-call (6 formats) | `failed=1` or `skipped=1` | User sees resend notice |\r\n| Approval-pending | `failed=1` | User sees resend notice |\r\n| Empty/uninspectable | `skipped=1` | User sees resend notice |\r\n\r\n## Security Impact\r\n\r\n- [x] New permissions/capabilities? No\r\n- [x] Secrets/tokens handling changed? No\r\n- [x] New/changed network calls? No\r\n- [x] Command/tool execution surface changed? No\r\n\r\n## AI Assistance\r\n\r\n- **AI-assisted**: Yes\r\n- **AI model**: deepseek-v4-pro\r\n\r\n---\r\nRelated to #95609 (text-only recovery — broader no-retype policy stays in #95609)\r\n",
        "branch": "fix/restart-recovery-user-retype-95609",
